FEATURES OF SQL :

Data Querying: Retrieves data.
Data Definition: Structures data.
Data Manipulation: Modifies data.
Transactions: Ensures consistency.
Data Integrity: Maintains accuracy.
Joins: Combines data.
Aggregation: Computes totals.
Subqueries: Nested queries.
Views: Virtual tables.
Procedures: Predefined tasks.
Indexing: Optimizes access.
Security: Controls access.
Concurrency: Manages access.